<p><blockquote>
<b><i>Between 1990 and 1994, small companies created five million new jobs. Fortune 500 companies lost 800,000 jobs. Guess which group received the most news coverage.  <P> A 1995 MediaNomics study showed that there were 119 stories in the first six months of that year about Fortune 500 layoffs. Only 13 stories mentioned job growth at other companies.
</b></i><br>
<ul></ul>
</blockquote>
