<HEAD><title>IRET</title>
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><font size=6><b><i>IRET</font><br>
<font size=4>Institute for Research on the Economics of Taxation<br>
</center></font></b></i><br>
<p>
The Institute for Research on the Economics of Taxation (IRET) is a 
non-profit, non-partisan, tax exempt 501(c)(3) public policy research 
organization devoted to informing the public about economic policies, 
especially those concerning the federal tax system, that will contribute 
to economic growth, efficiency and competitiveness.  To this end, IRET 
provides policy makers in the private as well as the public sector with 
objective, closely-reasoned analyses of the economic effects of public 
economic policy initiatives.<br>
<p>
Constructive public policies, in IRET's view, are those that reduce 
government interference in the operation of the private, free market 
system.  Such policies must recognize two basic facts of American 
economic life - one, that individuals' decisions about personal effort, 
saving, investment, and consumption, as reflected in voluntary and free 
exchange in the market place, provide the signals for efficient conduct 
of business, and two, that business is the prime mover on which the 
nation's economic progress depends.<br>

<p> 
<center><b>
IRET<br>
1300 19th Street, N.W., Suite 240<br>
Washington, D.C.  20036<br>
Phone: 202/463-1400 Fax: 202/463-6199<br></b>

<p>
