http://www.conservative.org:80/yaf/pres-m.html 204.71.237.88 19970208082212 text/html 6099
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Server: Netscape-Commerce/1.12
Date: Saturday, 08-Feb-97 08:22:57 GMT
Last-modified: Tuesday, 29-Oct-96 22:16:36 GMT
Content-length: 5913
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<html>
<head>
<title>President's Message</title>
</head>

<body background="/yaf/ground2.gif">


<img alt="Picutre of Reagan and Robinson" src="r&r.gif" align = ><br><h2>President's Message</h2>

You would be very disappointed if you knew what was going on in our schools.<p>

America's public schools and colleges have relinquished their role of defending and transmitting our history, religious heritage, and culture.<p>

Schools are hotbeds of violence, disrespect and failure.<p>

School administrators pass out condoms and teach "tolerance" for deviant lifestyles, but insist they can't "impose" religious values or even ask students to say the Pledge of Allegiance.<p>

Students learn the latest environmental theories but they aren't taught to adequately read, write, or add. <p>

College admissions programs and faculty hirings are rigged. It's better to be designated a member of an "oppressed" class than to be an honor student or an effective teacher.<p>

Our heroes are demeaned. Long-standing American role models are replaced with obscure but "politically correct" characters in a new "multicultural" curriculum.<p>

Thomas Sowell notes that every one of Karl Marx's works is available in our schools' bookstores. But Sowell no longer finds The Federalist Papers.<p>

The Bible is taboo; it's replaced in our grade schools with Heather Has Two Mommies!<p>

The Radical Left decided that its most important goal was to gain control of our educational system.<p>

Radical teachers and administrators promote an agenda that attacks traditional values, causes racial strife, and is preoccupied with envy and class warfare.<p>

Radical feminists institutionalize an anti-family agenda through "Women's Studies" departments and programs.<p>

Militant homosexuals design freshmen orientation programs to force acceptance of their lifestyles and consequently demand a ban on religiously oriented free speech.<p>

Leftist control is so complete that students on many campuses are denied the right to attend ROTC or they are told they cannot form religious clubs.<p>

At the University of Maryland students weren't permitted to display the American flag during the Persian Gulf war!<p>

In 1992 Bill Clinton spoke at fifty campuses, appeared on youth-related television programs, and otherwise targeted the student audience.<p>

President Clinton frequently dispatches his Administration's officials to the college campus, especially Hillary Clinton, Joycelyn Elders, Al Gore, and Robert Reich.<p>


College administrators who have a sordid history of violating students' Constitutional rights, as Donna Shalala did at the University of Wisconsin and Sheldon Hackney at the University of Pennsylvania, are given choice governmental positions.<p>

Our educational system, in which we invest our fortunes and our children, are controlled by people who are hostile to the values we hold dear.<p>

Most of us know there is a problem but we are tempted to underestimate how bad or how damaging it is. <p>

Abraham Lincoln expressed it best, "The philosophy of the school room in one generation will be the philosophy of government in the next."<p>

If that holds true, we are in for some very, very hard times.<p>

Can it be more obvious?<p>

Conservatives need to be more active in the education of our nation's young people.<p>

We must demand that our schools be balanced and fair institutions.<p>

That is the mission of Young America's Foundation.<p>

Unfortunately, those who control our schools are not about to voluntarily share power.<p>

In fact, one lesson conservatives have learned is that the Left covets a monopoly over information and education in America.<p>

Young America's Foundation's twenty-five year record is a history of struggle to break the Left's monopoly in our schools.<p>

Leading scholars and policy makers who lecture for the Foundation have made a dramatic impact. Recent nationwide tours by William F. Buckley, Jr., Dinesh D'Souza, Bay Buchanan, Edwin Meese, Bill Bennett, Walter Williams, and Oliver North have been large enough and effective enough to change our campuses for good.<p>

Young America's Foundation has benefited by the involvement and help of Ronald Reagan, Milton Friedman, Phyllis Schlafly, Patrick Buchanan, Dana Rohrabacher, Caspar Weinberger, Robert Dornan, Jeane Kirkpatrick, Jack Kemp, Phil Gramm, and Robert Novak.<p>
	
But it is the students, faculty members and financial supporters are the real heroes of Young America's Foundation's first twenty-five years.<p>

Students invest tremendous time and energy to put on our programs, publish independent papers and journals, and fight faculty and administration pressure to conform to a "politically correct" agenda. Often these young men and women make great personal sacrifices to participate in our activities.<p>

Conservative faculty members are a rare group indeed. Yet those who have dedicated their careers to truly educating their students merit our eternal gratitude. Many deserve mention but I am especially thankful for the help given by Burt Folsom, Forrest McDonald, Richard Ebeling, Walter Williams, Thomas DiLorenzo, Alan Sabrosky, Charles Kesler, Jeffrey Hart, the late Russell Kirk and M.E. Bradford.<p>

Financial supporters have made these programs possible. You have backed up these students and faculty members with the financial support their schools should have provided but didn't.  They have helped create a successful model to inform students of the greatness of our country, its free enterprise heritage, and our many blessings from God.<p>

Each of us must do more to achieve our goal of passing on a heritage of which we can be proud. But it is appropriate to take a short time to reflect on how far we have come. Thank you.<p><p>

[ <a href="home.html">Home</a> ]<p><p>

</body>
</html>
