<p>
<li>The population of the United States increased by  <font color="blue"><b>0.9% from July 1995 to July 1996</b></font>:
<p>
<center><font color="red"><h3>This includes the 855,648 immigrants who came to America during this time period.</h3></font>
</center>
<p>
<FONT SIZE=2>Source: Bureau of the Census</FONT>
<p>
<hr>
<p>
<li>Number of species of birds that <font color="red"><b>have become extinct</b></font> in America since the arrival of the Pilgrims:

<p>
<center><font color="blue"><h3> Four</h3></font>
</center>
<FONT SIZE=2>Source: David Rothbard and Craig Rucker, "While Biting the Hand that Feeds Us," <I>Wall Street Journal</I>, November 18 1996. </FONT><p>
<hr>
<p>
<li>There are <font color="blue"><b>two billion more songbirds in the U.S. than there were in the 16th century</b></font>.
<p>
<FONT SIZE=2>Source: David Rothbard and Craig Rucker, "While Biting the Hand that Feeds Us," <I>Wall Street Journal</I>, November 18 1996. </FONT>
<p>
