<html>
<head>
<title>CPAC '97</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<center>

<img src="/cpac/new-logo.gif" alt="CPAC "97"><p>
<h2>CPAC '97<br>
Twenty Four Years of Service to Conservative Principles</h2>
</center>

The "mainstream" of politics was a cliche -- much abused -- when in 1973 a handful of true believers in real values of America met in the Nation's capital. Their sole purpose was to affirm their support of the Conservative ideal. What they started -- with the first CPAC conference -- has become over the ensuing twenty-four years the <i>stellar</i> Conservative gathering of the year and one of the most important political events of both parties.<p>

CPAC is designed to advance important everyday issues such as taxes, crime, culture and foreign policy and to provide basic conservative viewpoints and solutions. CPAC '97 will be a three day event from Thursday, March 6, 1997 through Saturday, March 8, 1997 hosted at the Omni Shoreham Hotel in Washington, D.C.. The conference is composed of speeches, forums and panel discussions from recognized leaders in this country and is sponsored by the American Conservative Union in conjunction with <i>Human Events</i> and over sixty other co-sponsors.<p>

Its mushrooming growth attests not that the "right" has moved "center" but that Conservatism is the true nucleus of American thought. We may attribute its "sudden popularity" to the excesses of liberalism over many a year and we wouldn't be wrong ... although it runs deeper than that. America, itself, was founded on the principle of Conservatism and has yearned to return to that basic philosophy.<p>

The spectacular growth of CPAC anbd now the celebration of it's twenty-forth anniversary isn't all that surprising. Twenty-four years ago it was warranted and timely and today it remains the same. It was anything but a temporary swing of the pendulum, rather, a steady course set -- strengthened and renewed with each year's growing power of CPAC.<p>

In 1997 -- our 24th Annual Conference opens within two months of what we expect will be a <i>new</i> amininistration. We hope for an administration that is founded on Conservative ideals not dominated by liberalism as in the past four years. However, what will really make this country prosper and stand for freedom is an enthusiastic commitment to a Conservative philosophy by the men and women who make service to the freedom of this country their life's goal. You can be a part of that commitment. Join us at CPAC '97!!<p>

<center>
[ <a href="/cpac/"> CPAC Home</a> | <a href="/conservative/join.html.cgi">Join ACU</a> | <a href="/cpac/97.html">CPAC '97 Home</a> ]
</center>
</boday>
</html>


