<li>    Heritage Foundation calculation based in part on Bureau of Labor Statistics, "Employer Costs for Employee Compensation" data. Optional employer-provided benefits that account for another $3.26 per hour, or 19 percent of total compensation, are not included in the tax wedge but also increase the cost of labor.<p>
